Package: klue
Type: Package
Title: A Hybrid ML and Random-Utility Workflow for LCMNL Specification
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Oliver", "Frings",
                  email = "oliver.frings@agroparistech.fr",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Oliver Frings [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Oliver Frings <oliver.frings@agroparistech.fr>
Description: A reusable workflow for specifying latent class multinomial
    logit (LCMNL) models. Initialises the LCMNL multi-start from clusterings
    of respondents' revealed-preference signatures (kmeans, GMM, hierarchical,
    PAM), estimates LCMNL for a range of class counts, compares against an
    MMNL benchmark, and returns BIC / AIC / ICL / entropy summaries plus
    class-specific coefficients. Accepts arbitrary discrete-choice datasets
    in long or wide format with optional availability columns.
    Implements the workflow described in Frings (2026), "A Hybrid Machine
    Learning and Random Utility Framework for Latent Class Model Specification."
